1. User Interface (UI)

EN: User Interface (UI) is the space where humans interact with computers to operate and control a system.
中: 用户界面（User Interface，UI）是人类与计算机进行交互、操作和控制系统的空间。
Example: Website interface / 网站界面

2. Components of Computer User Interface

EN: User Interface includes all parts users can see, hear, or touch.
中: 用户界面包括用户可以看到、听到或触摸到的所有部分。
Example: Keyboard and screen / 键盘和屏幕

3. Human (User) Consideration in Interface Design

EN: Humans have limited ability to process information, so interfaces must be simple.
中: 人类处理信息的能力有限，因此界面设计应简洁。
Example: Simple layout / 简单布局

4. Human–Computer Interaction (HCI)

EN: Human–Computer Interaction (HCI) studies how people interact with computers to design better systems.
中: 人机交互（Human–Computer Interaction，HCI）研究人类如何与计算机互动，以设计更好的系统。
Example: User-friendly kiosk / 易用的自助机

5. Usability (ISO 9241-11)

EN: Usability is the extent to which users achieve goals with effectiveness, efficiency, and satisfaction.
中: 可用性（Usability）是用户以有效性、效率和满意度完成目标的程度。
Example: Easy-to-use app / 易用应用

6. Effectiveness

EN: Effectiveness is the accuracy and completeness of task completion.
中: 有效性（Effectiveness）指完成任务的准确性和完整性。
Example: Correct form submission / 正确提交表单

7. Efficiency

EN: Efficiency is the time and effort used to complete a task.
中: 效率（Efficiency）指完成任务所花费的时间和精力。
Example: Task done quickly / 快速完成任务

8. Satisfaction

EN: Satisfaction is how comfortable and happy users feel using a system.
中: 满意度（Satisfaction）指用户使用系统时的舒适与愉快程度。
Example: Enjoyable app / 用得舒服的应用

9. User Experience (UX)

EN: User Experience (UX) is the overall feeling when using a system.
中: 用户体验（User Experience，UX）是用户使用系统时的整体感受。
Example: Fun learning app / 有趣的学习应用

10. Relationship between Usability and User Experience

EN: Usability focuses on function, while user experience focuses on feeling.
中: 可用性关注功能，用户体验关注感受。
Example: Works but not enjoyable / 能用但不好用

11. Types of User Interfaces

Graphical User Interface (GUI): Uses icons and menus. 图形用户界面，通过图标和菜单交互。 Example: Windows / Windows 系统
Command-Line Interface (CLI): Uses text commands. 命令行界面，通过指令操作。 Example: Linux terminal / Linux 终端
Voice User Interface (VUI): Uses voice commands. 语音用户界面。 Example: Alexa / Alexa
Touch User Interface (TUI): Uses touch gestures. 触摸用户界面。 Example: Smartphone / 智能手机
Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality Interface (AR/VR): Immersive interaction. 增强/虚拟现实界面。 Example: VR game / VR 游戏

12. Evolution of User Interaction

EN: User interaction evolved with technology.
中: 用户交互方式随着技术发展而演变。
Example: Touchscreen phones / 触屏手机

13. Importance of Good User Interface Design

EN: Good design improves usability and satisfaction.
中: 良好设计提升可用性和满意度。
Example: Simple search page / 简洁搜索页

14. Effects of Poor User Interface Design

EN: Poor design causes errors and frustration.
中: 糟糕设计会造成错误和挫折感。
Example: Confusing buttons / 混乱按钮

15. Principles of Good User Interface Design

Consistency（一致性）, Feedback（反馈）, Simplicity（简洁）, Error Prevention（错误预防）, Accessibility（无障碍）
Examples: Progress bar / 进度条, Undo button / 撤销按钮

16. Human–Computer Interaction Design Framework

EN: Focuses on user-centered and iterative design.
中: 强调以用户为中心并反复改进。
Example: Test and improve / 测试并改进

17. Disciplines Contributing to Human–Computer Interaction

EN: Multiple disciplines support interaction design.
中: 多学科共同支持交互设计。
Examples: Computer Science / 计算机科学, Cognitive Psychology / 认知心理学, Ergonomics / 人体工学
